com.objetdirect.tatami.client.gfx
Class Pattern

java.lang.Object
  com.objetdirect.tatami.client.gfx.Pattern

public class Pattern
extends java.lang.Object

A pattern is an image which is used to fill a GraphicalOject. The pattern is applied until the GraphicalOject is fully filled.
Example :

GraphicalObject circle = new Circle(50);
Pattern pattern = new Pattern("icon.gif",0,0,10,10);
circle.applyPattern(pattern);

The pattern is prioritary on the backgroud color. To unuse the pattern, you need to apply the DEFAULT_PATTERN on the GraphicalObject
